<h2 id="present-continuous">Present Continuous</h2>

<p>Keep it simple. One of the most common ways to mark the future is to use <em>present continuous</em> with a <strong>temporal adverb</strong>.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p><em>Iâ€™m meeting</em> a friend for coffee <strong>tomorrow.</strong></p>
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
  <p><em>Sheâ€™s driving</em> into town <strong>tonight</strong>.</p>
